    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A dietician has to develop a special diet using two foods $$X$$ and $$Y$$. Each packet (containing $$30 \\mathrm{~g}$$ ) of food. $$X$$ contains 12 units of calcium, 4 units of iron, 6 units of cholesterol and 6 units of vitamin A. Each packet of the same quantity of food Y contains 3 units of calcium, 20 units of iron, 4 units of cholesterol and 3 units of vitamin A. The diet requires at least 240 units of calcium, atleast 460 units of iron and atmost 300 units of cholesterol. The corner points of the feasible region are</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$(2,72),(40,15),(15,20)$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$(2,72),(15,20),(0,23)$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$(0,23),(40,15),(2,72)$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$(2,72),(40,15),(115,0)$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Let $$x$$ and $$y$$ be the number of packets of food $$X$$ and $$Y$$</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{array}{ll} \n&amp; x \\geq 0, y \\geq 0 \\Rightarrow 12 x+3 y \\geq 240 \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad &amp; 4 x+y \\geq 80 \\quad \\text{.... (i)}\\\\\n&amp; 4 x+20 y \\geq 460 \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad &amp; x+5 y \\geq 115 \\quad \\text{.... (ii)}\\\\\n&amp; 6 x+4 y \\leq 300 \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad &amp; 3 x+2 y \\leq 150 \\quad \\text{.... (iii)}\\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad &amp; x \\geq 0, y \\geq 0 \\quad \\text{.... (iv)}\\\\\n&amp; 4 x+y \\geq 80\n\\end{array}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow$$ <style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 250px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 106px\">\n<col style=\"width: 73px\">\n<col style=\"width: 71px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">$$x$$</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">0</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">20</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$y$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">80</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">0</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>$$x+5y\\ge115$$</p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 250px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 106px\">\n<col style=\"width: 73px\">\n<col style=\"width: 71px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">$$x$$</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">0</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">115</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$y$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">23</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">0</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>$$3x+2y\\le150$$</p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 250px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 106px\">\n<col style=\"width: 73px\">\n<col style=\"width: 71px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">$$x$$</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">0</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">50</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$y$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">75</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">0</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>Intersection points of the lines are shown in the graph</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ltat1egp/d7fbc48a-abe8-40cd-b18e-254ad198d5c9/4a2af690-d8f9-11ee-bfea-0d7f65e800fb/file-6y3zli1ltat1egq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ltat1egp/d7fbc48a-abe8-40cd-b18e-254ad198d5c9/4a2af690-d8f9-11ee-bfea-0d7f65e800fb/file-6y3zli1ltat1egq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2022 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 13 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>we can see that corner point of the feasible region $$A, B$$ and $$C$$ are $$(2,72),(40,15),(15,20)$$.</p>",
