    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Lets draw the given shaded region,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltcfw1nl/fbe96a9d-0bb2-40e2-8978-14c1ddd72b09/6fd8fd10-d9df-11ee-9fe4-1197aa8394ec/file-1ltcfw1nm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltcfw1nl/fbe96a9d-0bb2-40e2-8978-14c1ddd72b09/6fd8fd10-d9df-11ee-9fe4-1197aa8394ec/file-1ltcfw1nm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 11 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Line $$l_1 \\Rightarrow \\frac{x}{4}+\\frac{y}{5}=1$$ (intercept form)</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\Rightarrow \\quad \\frac{5 x+4 y}{4 \\times 5}=1 \\\\\n&amp; \\Rightarrow \\quad 5 x+4 y=20\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>As, origin is not in the feasible region.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore \\quad 5 x+4 y \\geq 20$$</p>\n<p>Line $$l_2 \\Rightarrow y \\leq 3$$ (from the graph)</p>\n<p>Line $$l_3 \\Rightarrow x \\leq 6$$ (from the graph)</p>\n<p>and coordinate axes $$x \\geq 0, y \\geq 0$$</p>\n<p>Hence, inequalities are $$5 x+4 y \\geq 20, y \\leq 3, x \\leq 6, x \\geq 0, y \\geq 0$$.</p>",
