    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The feasible region of an LPP is shown in the figure. If $$z=11 x+7 y$$, then the maximum value of $$Z$$ occurs at</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltilugub/976ab77c-1fb0-48e7-94de-969be092e9a8/6ea1f840-dd43-11ee-a15a-af8e132f1b6d/file-1ltiluguc.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltilugub/976ab77c-1fb0-48e7-94de-969be092e9a8/6ea1f840-dd43-11ee-a15a-af8e132f1b6d/file-1ltiluguc.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2020 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 9 English\"></p>",
