    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>From the given shaded region, we have</p>\n<p>$$\\frac{x}{10}+\\frac{y}{3}=1 \\Rightarrow 3 x+10 y=30\\quad \\text{..... (i)}$$</p>\n<p>Since, feasible region towards the origin</p> \n<p>$$\\therefore$$ required inequality $$3 x+10 y \\leq 30$$</p>\n<p>Now, $$\\frac{x}{5}+\\frac{y}{4}=1 \\Rightarrow 4 x+5 y=20\\quad \\text{.... (ii)}$$</p>\n<p>Since, feasible region away from the origin :required inequality $$4 x+5 y \\geq 20$$</p>\n<p>And also, $$x \\leq 6 ; x, y \\geq 0$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ required inequalities are\n$$3 x+10 y \\leq 30 ; 4 x+5 y \\geq 20 ; x \\leq 6 ; x, y \\geq 0$$</p>",
