    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9cid0wh/bf834359-5103-4825-9212-2df8fb6495cc/90579410-16ac-11f0-ab51-03ccb4d25766/file-jaoe38c1m9cid0wi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9cid0wh/bf834359-5103-4825-9212-2df8fb6495cc/90579410-16ac-11f0-ab51-03ccb4d25766/file-jaoe38c1m9cid0wi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2017 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 4 English Explanation\">\n<p>Equation of line $L_1$ is given by</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{array}{rlrl}  &amp; &amp; y-0 &amp; =\\frac{5-0}{0-4}(x-4) \\\\ \\Rightarrow &amp; &amp; y &amp; =\\frac{-5}{4}(x-4) \\\\ \\Rightarrow &amp; &amp; 4 y &amp; =-5 x+20 \\\\ \\Rightarrow &amp; 5 x+4 y &amp; =20 \\end{array} $$</p>\n<p>Since, $(0,0)$ and shaded region lies on opposite sides, so we have one inequation</p>\n<p>$$ 5 x+4 y \\geq 20 $$</p>\n<p>Now, equation of line $L_2$ is $y=3$. Since shaded region and $(0,0)$ lies on same side, so we have second inequation</p>\n<p>$$ y \\leq 3 $$</p>\n<p>Again, equation of line $L_3$ is $x=6$. Since, shaded region and $(0,0)$ lies on same side, so we have third inequation</p>\n<p>$$ x \\leq 6 $$</p>\n<p>Also, shaded region lies in first quadrant, so $x \\geq 0, y \\geq 0$.</p>",
